The retailer, known for its posh wellies, hired KPMG to help boost profits and shore up its balance sheet. Reports said bosses were considering raising fresh capital. Joules said in May that boss Nick Jones would step down in the first half of its next financial year while warning of the impact on profits of the cost-of-living crisis. Its share price has plummeted by more than 80 percent in the year to date. Joules said: "The group continues to focus on improving profitability, cash generation and liquidity headroom."